# Bids Pipeline Guidance

- Treat `deal-extraction-skills/` as the reference workflow and artifact
  contract.
- Project-local Cursor skill wrappers live in `.cursor/skills/`; read the
  canonical vendored skill under `deal-extraction-skills/skills/` when using
  one of those wrappers.
- Treat `pipeline/` as the Python implementation attempt, not a proven
  end-to-end system.
- Use filing text as the only factual source of truth.
- Keep every extracted fact traceable to `source_accession_number` and verbatim
  `source_text`.
- Keep facts separate from judgments: proposals are raw events first, then
  classification and boundary logic later.
- Never rewrite frozen filing `.txt` snapshots downstream.
- Prefer deterministic Python logic for policy rules and audits.
- Preserve range-bid information and typed provenance fields.
- Do not use Alex's notes or spreadsheets as factual evidence for a deal.
- Remember the main current gaps: no concrete `Provider`, incomplete
  supplementary filing support, and incomplete `actors_extended.jsonl`
  integration.
